{
  "text": "We can then define the notion of a holomorphic bundle E but note that in [CITATION_1] the basic definition of this is given in terms of a left holomorphic section. This awkwardly lends itself to looking at hermitian inner products with the antilinear side on the right, which is opposite to the usual convention for the Dirac operator. However, in the spinor bundle case we can use the antilinear isomorphism j \u2236 S \u2192 S to swap the side of the antilinear part by commutativity of the following diagram:",
